25|$|In 2006, then California Governor Arnold Schwarzenegger {{broke from}} Republican orthodoxy to sign several bills {{imposing}} caps on carbon emissions in California. George W. Bush, then U.S. President, opposed mandatory caps {{at a national}} level. Bush's decision not to regulate carbon dioxide as a pollutant was challenged {{in the supreme court}} by 12 states, with the court ruling against <b>the</b> <b>Bush</b> <b>administration</b> <b>in</b> 2007. Bush also publicly opposed ratification of the Kyoto Protocols which sought to limit greenhouse gas emissions and thereby combat climate change, a decision heavily criticized by climate scientists.|$|E
